File: South African comedian Trevor Noah has been nominated for a Grammy. JOHANNESBURG - Daily Show host Trevor Noah has paid tribute to audience members with a song, as the show prepares to ban live audiences amid coronavirus fears. Noah revealed that the show will no longer tape with a live studio audience from Monday in order to combat the spread of the coronavirus. READ: Trevor Noah makes history at sold-out Madison Square Garden The outbreak has affected the production of popular TV shows, with many hosts announcing that shows will either be suspended or be taped without an audience. Noah decided to bid farewell to his audience with a special song. With The Daily Show going audience-free for a while, we pay tribute to the audience members we’ll miss the most. #TheDailyShow #DailyShow #TrevorNoah